	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Curtius, 5.3.4‑15</A>;
Arrian, 3.17<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note22" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref22
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">22</A>
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/5*.html#3.17
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Curtius, 5.3.17</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note23" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref23
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">23</A>
Arrian's account
(3.18)
	<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->
explains that Alexander had sent on his main body of troops toward Persis along the royal road, and only undertook this pass with a flying column.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note24" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref24
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">24</A>
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/5*.html#3.17
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Curtius, 5.3.17
	</A>
(25,000 infantry);
Arrian, 3.18.2
	<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->
(40,000 infantry and 700 cavalry).


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note25" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref25
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">25</A>
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/5*.html#3.17
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Curtius, 5.3.17‑23</A>, more reasonably, says thirty furlongs.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note26" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref26
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">26</A>
Strictly speaking, that is, he knew Persian and Lycian
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/5.html#37
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Plutarch, <I>Alexander</I>, 37.1)</A>, but Curtius
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/5*.html#4.4
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(5.4.4)
	</A>
adds more relevantly that he also knew Greek.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note27" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref27
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">27</A>
This is a somewhat unexpected term which editors have viewed with suspicion, but a path which follows folds in the mountains is often marked by vegetation. Curtius
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/5*.html#4.24
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(5.4.24)
	</A>
locates these bushes in a great ravine.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note28" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref28
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">28</A>
	<A HREF="
