Plutarch, <I>Alexander</I>, 42.3‑43.3</A>;
Arrian, 3.19‑22<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->. The standard version in all is that Dareius was still living when discovered, but died before Alexander saw him. Plutarch, <I>De Fortuna aut Virtute Alexandri</I>, on the other


<A ID="p329x"></A>hand, has Alexander covering Dareius with his own cloak
	<A HREF="
