<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note57" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref57
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">57</A>
These were the troops furnished according to their decision


<A ID="p331x"></A>by the members of the Hellenic League (Books <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/16D*.html#89.3
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">16.89.3</A>;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17A*.html#4.9
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
17.4.9</A>). Curtius
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/6*.html#2.17
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(6.2.17)</A>, also, reports their dismissal at this time; their mission was complete with the destruction of Persepolis and the death of Dareius. Arrian
(3.19.5)
	<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->
places their dismissal earlier, at Ecbatana.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note58" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref58
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">58</A>
Curtius
	<A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/6*.html#2.17
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(6.2.17)
	</A>
gives this figures. These sums are much larger than those distributed at Babylon
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#64.6
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(chap. 64.6)</A>. One may wonder whether Alexander could have been so generous to Greeks without taking care of the Macedonians equally well.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
