Arrian, 3.25.1‑7<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note88" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref88
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">88</A>
Arrian
(3.25.8)
	<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->
calls these people "Zarangaioi." The usual term is Drangianê.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note89" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref89
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">89</A>
Diodorus has compressed the movements involved in this operation. Alexander had left Hyrcania and passed through Parthia and Aria, where he left Satibarzanes as satrap. He advanced east toward Bactria. At the revolt of Satibarzanes, he returned to Aria; the satrap in his flight must have passed Alexander going in the opposite direction. He can have encountered Satibarzanes's foot troops in the mountains east of Artacoana and not have proceeded to that city. Finally, after thirty days, he turned south into Drangianê, abandoning his original route.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note90" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref90
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">90</A>
For the story of the conspiracy and its consequences cp. <A HREF="
L/Roman/Texts/Curtius/6*.html#7
	"TARGET="Curtius"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef1,WIDTH,155)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Curtius, 6.7-7.2.34</A>;
	<A HREF="
https://www.forumromanum.org/literature/justin/texte12.html#5
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,LatinRef2PlusTranslation,WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Justin, 12.5.1‑3</A>;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/6-7.html#48
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Plutarch, <I>Alexander</I>, 48‑49.7</A>;
Arrian, 3.26<!--</A>ARRIAN3-->.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note91" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17D*.html#ref91
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
